<HEAD>European Community Has Given $37.8 Million for Armenian Quake Victims</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The European Economic Community and its
member states have given $37.8 million for victims of the earthquake
in Armenia.
   The community gave $11.4 million in emergency aid, and all 12
member states, except Italy, donated additional aid totaling $26.4
million, the EEC said.
   It had no figure for Italian aid of four flights with emergency
equipment, medicines and 30 medical staffers.
   Total foreign assistance for victims of the Dec. 7 earthquake was
$65.7 million, the commission said.
   The community and its members sent thousands of tents, blankets,
heating and power equipment, beds, medical equipment, medicines,
clothes, prefabricated buildings and vehicles to Armenia by air and
road.
