<HEAD>Gale-Force Winds Carry Dust From Sahara to Czechoslovakia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PRAGUE, Czechoslovakia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dirty rain, believed to carry sand
from the Sahara Desert, covered houses, cars and umbrellas in
central Slovakia with a thin layer of dust, a newspaper reported
Monday.
   Samples of the rain were analyzed by public health monitors in
Poprad, 125 miles northwest of Bratislava. A similar phenomenon was
recorded 13 years ago when dust from the Sahara was carried through
the atmosphere into the High Tatras, Czechoslovakia's highest
mountain region and a resort with a national park.
   The mountains also were hit by winds of up to 90 mph, the
newspaper Lidova Demokracie said. It did not mention any injuries or
casualties.
