<SECOND>AM-BRF--Peru-Bus,0132</SECOND>
<HEAD>Peruvian Bus Crash Kills 16</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIMA, Peru (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two buses collided head-on in the outskirts of
the capital Monday, killing 16 people and seriously injuring seven,
after one of the vehicles struck a motorcyclist and lost control,
police said.
   The motorcyle rider ran a stop sign and crossed the intersection
in front of a small bus, whose driver tried to avoid the motorcycle
but hit it. The bus careened into a full-sized bus coming in the
opposite direction.
   Police said the small bus was traveling at excessive speed and
carrying 22 passengers, five more than its legal capacity.
   All of those killed were riding in the smaller bus, as were all
those seriously hurt, with the exception of the motorcyclist, police
said.
</TEXT>
