<FIRST>u i AM-Peru 1stLd-Writethru a0724 02-27 0321</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Peru, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0724,0326</SECOND>
<HEAD>Seven Rebels, Three Soldiers Die in Peruvian Ambush</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS throughout, UPDATING with seven rebels killed, other details.
No pickup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AYACUCHO, Peru (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three soldiers and seven Maoist guerrillas
were killed when rebels ambushed an army truck on a mountain road
near this state capital, officials said Monday.
   Five soldiers and ``numerous'' rebels were wounded in the
fighting Sunday at an isolated spot in Peru's southern highlands, a
military communique said.
   Elsewhere, authorities said security forces fatally shot five
suspected members of the Shining Path guerrilla group on Monday when
they burst into a house on the outskirts of Huancayo, a major city
in the central Andes 140 miles east of Lima.
   Civilian court officials said about 20 police and soldiers
wearing hoods barged in after receiving information guerrillas were
using it as a safe house.
   The local district attorney's office said it was not clear if the
five young men were armed. Police and the military refused to
provide information on the shooting.
   In other violence, police said Shining Path rebels on Monday
killed the mayor of Mantaro, a district 20 miles north of Huancayo.
They said two men and a woman shot Teodoro Tovar, a member of the
governing center-left Aprista Party.
   A military communique issued in Ayacucho said the guerrilla
ambush of the army truck occurred shortly before nightfall Sunday 20
miles northeast of Ayacucho. The provincial capital lies 235 miles
southest of Lima.
   The report said a truck carrying 15 soldiers to the nearby army
post of Julcamarca was caught in a cross fire by about 50 rebels
positioned on slopes above the road.
   The wounded were evacuated to Ayacucho, an old colonial town that
was the birthplace of the Shining Path insurgency nine years ago.
   Since 1980, more than 12,000 people have died in Peru's political
violence and the Shining Path has expanded its insurgency throughout
this impoverished country.
</TEXT>
