prevented banks, that were otherwise inclined to do so, from
participating in a wide range of negotiated debt reduction
transactions with borrowing countries,'' three regulatory agencies
said in a report Friday to the Senate Banking Committee.
   Critics of current policy say banks should be permitted to spread
the effects of recognizing losses over several years. Currently,
they must reduce profita by the full amount of any addition to loss
reserves.
