<FIRST>u f AM-WPPGroup-Canada     02-27 0257</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-WPP Group-Canada,0266</SECOND>
<HEAD>WPP Group Buys One Of Canada's Largest PR Agencies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   WPP Group PLC of London said Monday it has agreed
to buy PARG Public Affairs Resource Group of Toronto, one of
Canada's largest public affairs consulting and public opinion
research firms.
   WPP Group said the deal will make its Hill and Knowlton (Canada)
Ltd. subsidiary the largest public relations firm in Canada.
   Terms of the deal were not disclosed, but the companies said in a
statement that it included cash and stock and possible additional
payouts over the next five years.
   WPP Group, the parent of the J. Walter Thompson advertising
company, said it will combine the operations of the Canadian agency
with its Hill and Knowlton Inc., an international public relations
and public affairs firm based in New York.
   Under terms of the agreement, WPP said it plans to combine the
operations of three PARG subsidiaries _ Public Affairs
International, Decima Research and Public Affairs Communication
Management _ with those of Hill and Knowlton (Canada) Ltd.
   ``PARG brings new dimensions to our already sizeable public
relations services in Canada,'' said Robert L. Dilenschneider,
president and chief executive of Hill and Knowlton in New York.
   The expanded orgnaization will have revenue of about 25 million
Canadian dollars, or about $21 million, this year, the statement
said. It will employ about 200 people in offices in Toronto, Ottawa,
Montreal, Vancouver and Calgary.
   The fourth PARG unit, Government Research Corp. of Washington,
D.C., will become part of Hill and Knowlton's Washington office.
</TEXT>
